                                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 (Potsdam)/5–2446</note>
                                <head>No. 435<lb/><hi rend="italic">Briefing Book Paper</hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]<note n="1" xml:id="d435fn1">For other sections of this paper, see <ref target="#d483">documents Nos. 483</ref>, <ref target="#d510">510</ref>, and <ref target="#d521">521</ref>.</note></seg>
                                </opener>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#left">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                                    </seg>
                                </opener>
                                <p rend="center">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Suggested United States Policy Regarding
                                        Poland</hi>
                                </p>
                                <p rend="center">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">summary</hi>
                                </p>
                                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                                <p>… We should facilitate insofar as our aid is requested the
                                    transfer of minority groups but we should not permit the forced
                                    repatriation of Poles now in the West or the uncontrolled
                                    deportation by unilateral Polish action of the 8–10,000,000
                                    Germans formerly domiciled in the areas claimed by the
                                    Soviet-sponsored Polish Government.</p>
                                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <dateline rendition="#left">[<placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-29">June 29, 1945</date>.</dateline>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
